===Etymology 3===
[[File:Shogi narigin(svg).svg|thumb|100px]]
From the resemblance of the character written on the reverse side of a [[silver general]], originally a cursive form of {{m|ja|金|tr=kin|t=gold}}, to a different character, namely {{lang|ja|全}}.

Reinterpreted as {{m|ja|銀|tr=gin|t=silver}} with strokes removed, and similar workarounds would be used to create {{l-self|ja|圭}} for {{m|ja|成桂|tr=narikei|t=promoted knight}}, and {{l-self|ja|杏}} for {{m|ja|成香|tr=narikyō|t=promoted lance}}.
